1. What is HTTP

HTTP (Hypertext Transfer Protocol) is a cleartext client-server protocol used to deliver web content.

Because it is unencrypted, analysts can inspect:
URLs
Headers
User agents
Form data
Payloads

Common Threats Detectable
Phishing websites
Web exploitation
Data exfiltration

Command & Control (C2)

2. Basic HTTP Filters
Show HTTP traffic
http
HTTP/2 traffic
http2
3. HTTP Request Methods
GET
Request data from server.
http.request.method == "GET"
POST
Send data to server (often login forms, uploads).
http.request.method == "POST"
Show all HTTP requests
http.request

4. Important HTTP Response Codes
Code	Meaning
200	OK
301	Moved permanently
302	Redirect
400	Bad request
401	Unauthorized
403	Forbidden
404	Not found
405	Method not allowed
408	Timeout
500	Internal server error
503	Service unavailable

Example filters:

http.response.code == 200
http.response.code == 404
http.response.code == 503

5. Important HTTP Parameters
User-Agent
Identifies browser / tool.
http.user_agent
URI (requested resource)
http.request.uri
Example:
http.request.uri contains "admin"
Full URL
http.request.full_uri
Host
http.host
Example:
http.host contains "example"
Server software
http.server contains "apache"

6. User-Agent Analysis
The User-Agent field can reveal tools used by attackers.
Example malicious tools:
Nmap
sqlmap
Nikto
Wfuzz
Filter:
(http.user_agent contains "sqlmap") or 
(http.user_agent contains "Nmap") or 
(http.user_agent contains "Wfuzz") or 
(http.user_agent contains "Nikto")
Suspicious Signs
Different user agents from the same IP quickly
Misspelled user agents
Scanner tools
Payload inside user-agent
Example:
Mozlila
instead of
Mozilla
7. Log4Shell (Log4j) Detection
Log4Shell exploit often appears in HTTP POST requests.
Indicators
jndi:ldap
Exploit.clas
Filters
POST requests:
http.request.method == "POST"
Search exploit strings:

frame contains "jndi"
frame contains "Exploit"
Suspicious User-Agent
(http.user_agent contains "$") or (http.user_agent contains "==")
